12:59.411 --> 13:02.613
Teller, is there anything else
in there?

13:02.681 --> 13:05.016
Pick it up.
- It's rock paper scissors.

13:05.083 --> 13:06.417
- Aw.
- Scissors. Okay.

13:06.419 --> 13:08.920
Just keep the scissors.
Alyson, take a look inside,

13:08.987 --> 13:10.621
and remove--well,
you figure it out.

13:10.689 --> 13:13.625
It's paper, and sit down.

13:13.692 --> 13:16.728
And can you remove the box?
Move it away.

13:17.829 --> 13:20.231
As you can see, we have rock,
paper, scissors,

13:20.233 --> 13:21.732
as it's called.

13:21.734 --> 13:24.302
Now, rock paper scissors--
It is one of the oldest games

13:24.369 --> 13:26.004
known to mankind.

13:26.071 --> 13:28.539
It dates back to the stone age
when it was called

13:28.607 --> 13:30.041
rock rock and rock

13:30.108 --> 13:31.910
usually ending up in a tie.

13:32.611 --> 13:35.046
Now, eventually the game has
evolved to rock paper scissors,

13:35.113 --> 13:37.381
and when we play
this game in Norway

13:37.383 --> 13:39.083
we always play best
out of three.

13:39.919 --> 13:43.120
Now, today,
I'm gonna take a huge risk,

13:43.122 --> 13:45.890
and I'm gonna get this
right three out of three.

13:45.958 --> 13:48.459
And if I make one mistake,
if I get one wrong,

13:48.526 --> 13:51.262
I'm gonna thank you humbly
for your time and say goodbye.

13:51.330 --> 13:52.797
- Okay.

13:52.864 --> 13:54.499
- Now, for the first round,

13:55.667 --> 13:58.336
two of you are
going to switch items.

