21:53.079 --> 21:58.849
But maybe I can turn that "no"
into a "yes" too.

21:58.917 --> 22:02.386
[cheers and applause]

22:02.453 --> 22:06.824
- Please welcome Chicago's
own Benjamin Barnes.

22:08.427 --> 22:10.161
- Hello, Penn and Teller.

22:10.228 --> 22:12.429
My name is Benjamin Barnes.

22:12.431 --> 22:17.067
International magic man
of mystery.

22:17.069 --> 22:19.269
And the piece of magic
I'll be doing tonight

22:19.337 --> 22:21.505
is truly a mystery.

22:21.507 --> 22:24.708
It works each and every time
that I do it,

22:24.710 --> 22:28.512
but I still can't
figure out how.

22:28.580 --> 22:30.414
Hopefully, the two of you

22:30.481 --> 22:32.850
won't be able to figure it out
either,

22:32.917 --> 22:35.152
but the way I see it,
no matter what,

22:35.219 --> 22:38.789
when I walk off this stage,
I'll be the winner.

22:38.856 --> 22:40.557
Because if you are able
to figure out

22:40.625 --> 22:41.925
how my magic is done,

22:41.927 --> 22:45.929
then I will have
finally learned its secret.

22:45.931 --> 22:48.999
And if you can't,
I get a "Fool Us" trophy,

22:49.001 --> 22:51.468
which would be unbelievable.

22:51.536 --> 22:53.404
Of course, I don't want
to do this alone.

22:53.471 --> 22:54.938
Alyson, will you please join me?

22:54.940 --> 22:55.939
- Yes.

22:55.941 --> 22:57.374
- Great. Hi.
- Hi.

22:57.376 --> 22:59.009
- Hi.
- Nice to meet you.

22:59.077 --> 23:00.411
- A pleasure.

23:00.478 --> 23:03.414
Now, Alyson, in the left hand
are the blue cards.

23:03.448 --> 23:06.049
There are 52, in total.

23:06.051 --> 23:09.219
I'll be using four.

23:09.287 --> 23:10.621
The four queens.

