Now, Alyson, I still need you
to pick one of these cards.

23:53.766 --> 23:57.468
I'm gonna pull cards from the
face of the pack, one by one,

23:57.535 --> 24:00.370
and I want you to focus
on the number cards.

24:00.372 --> 24:01.605
- Okay.

24:01.673 --> 24:04.274
- When you see one
that you like say, "Stop."

24:04.276 --> 24:05.876
- Okay.

24:08.579 --> 24:09.480
- Stop.

24:09.547 --> 24:10.581
- Right here?
- Yes.

24:10.648 --> 24:12.749
- All right.
Pick up the pen, Alyson,

24:12.817 --> 24:14.685
and write your initials
in large letters

24:14.752 --> 24:18.755
across the face of the card.

24:18.823 --> 24:21.091
Perfect.
Now, one of the reasons

24:21.093 --> 24:24.161
why I wanted Alyson
to focus on the number cards

24:24.163 --> 24:26.096
is because of the white space,

24:26.163 --> 24:29.600
which makes it easier for us
to see her initials there,

24:29.667 --> 24:30.934
on the four of diamonds.

24:31.002 --> 24:33.504
Now, Alyson,
what I'd like for you to do

24:33.571 --> 24:34.771
is to hold the cards.

24:34.839 --> 24:36.807
Put your other hand
right on top. Perfect.

24:36.874 --> 24:40.143
And at this time,
I'd like to remind everyone

24:40.211 --> 24:43.347
that I have the four queens.

24:43.414 --> 24:46.383
Alyson, I'm gonna place
your four of diamonds

24:46.450 --> 24:48.952
into the center
of the four queens,

24:49.020 --> 24:53.857
and Penn and Teller, it's plain
to see that's no mystery.

24:53.925 --> 24:56.793
Now, Alyson,
to make the magic work,

24:56.795 --> 25:00.331
you need to say
the mystery word.

25:00.398 --> 25:01.598
- Okay.

25:01.666 --> 25:03.267
- What is the mystery word,
you might ask?

25:03.269 --> 25:05.168
- Yes. What is the mystery
word?

25:05.236 --> 25:06.870
- I have no idea.
- Oh, dear.

25:06.872 --> 25:08.739
- Because it's a--
- Mystery!

25:08.741 --> 25:10.207
- Exactly.

25:10.275 --> 25:15.546
Alyson, I want you to think
of your very own mystery word.

25:15.613 --> 25:18.615
Don't say it.
We want to keep it a--

25:18.617 --> 25:20.084
- Mystery.

25:20.151 --> 25:22.819
- In a moment, I'm gonna extend
these five cards

25:22.887 --> 25:24.221
in Alyson's direction.

25:24.289 --> 25:26.490
Alyson, when that happens
I want you

25:26.492 --> 25:31.028
to say your mystery word
as mysteriously as you can.

25:31.030 --> 25:32.463
- Okay.

25:32.530 --> 25:35.299
- And as unbelievable as it
might sound, at that moment,

25:35.301 --> 25:39.002
one of the five cards
will vanish without a trace.

25:39.070 --> 25:39.970
- Hmm.
- You ready?

25:40.038 --> 25:41.839
- I'm ready.

25:41.906 --> 25:44.041
Cookie.

25:44.108 --> 25:45.576
- It's done.

25:45.643 --> 25:47.978
Where there were once
five cards there are now one,

25:48.046 --> 25:52.516
two, three, four queens.

25:52.584 --> 25:57.921
And Alyson, your card
has completely vanished.

25:57.989 --> 26:00.090
Where did it go? That's a--

26:00.157 --> 26:01.325
- Mystery.

26:01.327 --> 26:05.362
- Let's see if we can
solve this mystery.

26:05.364 --> 26:08.198
Alyson, raise your hand.

26:08.265 --> 26:11.468
Inside of the pack
that you've been holding onto

26:11.535 --> 26:16.273
this entire time
is a mystery card

26:16.341 --> 26:22.079
which has been there
since the very start.

26:22.146 --> 26:24.147
Penn and Teller,
you won't believe this,

26:24.149 --> 26:26.283
but the mystery card
is none other

26:26.351 --> 26:28.686
than Alyson's four of diamonds.

26:28.753 --> 26:31.455
And that is a true...

26:31.522 --> 26:33.557
both: Mystery.

26:33.624 --> 26:35.359
[cheers and applause]

26:35.426 --> 26:39.730
- Thank you. Thank you.
- Benjamin Barnes!

26:39.797 --> 26:42.966
- Fantastic.
- Oh, that was really good.

26:42.968 --> 26:44.568
- Thank you. Thank you.

26:44.636 --> 26:46.403
- I heard from Penn
and Teller Chicago

26:46.470 --> 26:48.672
is just known
for brilliant magicians.

26:48.739 --> 26:50.441
- Yes, yes. It's a long history

26:50.508 --> 26:54.378
that goes back--at
least as far back as 1898.

26:54.380 --> 26:55.712
- Wow.
- Chicago gave birth

26:55.780 --> 26:57.714
to bar magic
and what we now think of

26:57.782 --> 26:59.750
as close-up magic,
so I was very lucky...

26:59.817 --> 27:00.718
- Yeah.
- To have grown up there.

27:00.785 --> 27:02.052
- Is that intimidating though,

27:02.120 --> 27:05.422
because you have
such big shoes to fill?

27:05.489 --> 27:08.258
- No. They're there for me
to put on, you know?

27:08.325 --> 27:09.526
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

27:09.528 --> 27:11.629
Those people--they established
this history.

27:11.663 --> 27:14.598
They pass on to me.
I pass it on to the next.

27:14.666 --> 27:15.732
- Yeah.

27:15.800 --> 27:17.801
- This is far more intimidating.

27:17.803 --> 27:22.706
- Oh, really? What is your most
memorable performance?

27:22.774 --> 27:24.074
- One of my first shows.

27:24.142 --> 27:26.576
My first show before an audience

27:26.644 --> 27:30.013
was in a rehabilitation center
for children.

27:30.081 --> 27:31.248
- Aw.

27:31.315 --> 27:34.551
- And none of the kids
could move or talk,

27:34.618 --> 27:36.019
and I went in.

27:36.087 --> 27:38.789
I was terrified, because
I was not prepared for that,

27:38.856 --> 27:41.124
and we did the show.
And by the end of it,

27:41.126 --> 27:43.027
while they couldn't talk
they could laugh.

27:43.094 --> 27:44.228
- Aw.

27:44.295 --> 27:46.830
- They could smile,
and never forget it.

27:46.897 --> 27:49.399
- Oh, that's amazing.
- Yeah.

27:49.401 --> 27:50.867
- Okay, Benjamin. Let's see

27:50.935 --> 27:54.071
if Penn and Teller have solved
the mystery of your trick.

27:54.138 --> 27:55.973
- Let's see.
- Oh, Benjamin.

27:56.040 --> 27:58.375
Boy, good magicians
out of Chicago, huh?

27:58.377 --> 27:59.843
- Yeah.
- Really good.

27:59.845 --> 28:01.145
- Oh, yeah.

28:01.212 --> 28:02.513
- And you're one of 'em.
- Thank you very much.

28:02.580 --> 28:03.847
- You're one of the
good magicians out of Chicago.

28:03.915 --> 28:05.449
- I appreciate it.
- And I'll tell you that stuff

28:05.451 --> 28:08.351
there--neither
one of us can do any of it.

28:08.419 --> 28:10.387
You just did that beautifully.

28:10.454 --> 28:11.488
- Thank you...
- Now...

28:11.556 --> 28:12.756
- So much.
- Know--I'm sure you know

28:12.823 --> 28:16.927
very well that our mentor,
our dear friend--

28:16.994 --> 28:19.596
And he was
with the show for many years.

28:19.664 --> 28:21.031
Johnny Thompson.
- Oh, yeah.

28:21.033 --> 28:23.200
- He showed us a lot of magic.
- Yeah.

28:23.267 --> 28:25.302
- He showed us
a lot of card magic

28:25.369 --> 28:27.170
that we could not do,

28:27.238 --> 28:29.706
and he explained it to us
over and over again,

28:29.708 --> 28:32.209
and we tried,
and we just couldn't do it.

28:32.276 --> 28:36.013
And the stuff you're doing
is so, so clean there,

28:36.080 --> 28:38.348
and I'll tell you,
I love watching it.

28:38.415 --> 28:40.016
I could watch you forever,
and I know

28:40.018 --> 28:43.220
you started this whole thing
by saying you won either way.

28:43.222 --> 28:44.654
- Yeah.
- Because it was a mystery.

28:44.722 --> 28:45.723
- Yes.

28:45.757 --> 28:46.957
- And you didn't know
how it was done,

28:47.024 --> 28:49.226
and that if we could tell you
how it was done,

28:49.228 --> 28:50.627
you'd have that mystery solved.

28:50.694 --> 28:53.330
Well, I'm just not gonna
spew out how it's done.

28:53.397 --> 28:54.698
That would ruin the fun...
- Yes.

28:54.766 --> 28:56.567
- So we have made
a quick phone call.

28:56.634 --> 28:57.601
- Okay.

28:57.635 --> 28:58.969
- And we have put
the information

28:59.036 --> 29:04.141
on how this trick is done
in escrow with our law firm

29:04.208 --> 29:08.345
Hammond, Elmsley, and Elmsley,
and we count Elmsley twice.

29:08.347 --> 29:10.848
So if you want to find out
how this was done,

29:10.915 --> 29:13.650
Benjamin, you go to Hammond,
Elmsley, and Elmsley,

29:13.652 --> 29:16.453
and tell 'em Penn and Teller
left a secret

29:16.521 --> 29:18.756
from Johnny Thompson in escrow.

29:18.823 --> 29:19.890
- I'll do that.

29:19.957 --> 29:21.258
- But I don't think
you fooled us.

29:21.260 --> 29:22.326
- I don't think so, either,

29:22.393 --> 29:23.894
but it was so awesome
to be here.

29:23.961 --> 29:24.961
- Thank you.
- Thank you, Ben.

29:25.029 --> 29:26.062
- Thank you so much.
- Great job.

29:26.064 --> 29:27.998
- Aw, thank you.
Benjamin Barnes.

29:28.065 --> 29:30.334
- Thank you, Alyson.
Thank you, guys. Thank you.

29:30.401 --> 29:32.536
Thank you.
[cheers and applause]

29:34.071 --> 29:37.073
- Penn and Teller might give
away another "Fool Us" trophy,

29:37.141 --> 29:39.676
but they're definitely
performing later tonight.

29:39.678 --> 29:41.645
More magic in a minute.

29:41.712 --> 29:43.280
[cheers and applause]

29:43.347 --> 29:46.316
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:49.187 --> 29:50.987
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:51.055 --> 29:54.424
[cheers and applause]

29:54.491 --> 29:56.360
- Welcome back.
Did you miss us?

29:56.427 --> 29:59.062
Well, you don't want
to miss this next act.

30:01.332 --> 30:03.166
- I'm Jamie Docherty.
- And I'm Lewis Joss.

30:03.168 --> 30:05.235
<i>- And we are Jay and Joss.</i>

30:05.302 --> 30:08.572
- Jay and I started out
as rival magicians.

30:08.639 --> 30:10.340
- Yeah. I was doing okay
in Northamptonshire.

30:10.407 --> 30:12.375
- Hey, I wasn't doing too bad
in Bedfordshire.

30:12.377 --> 30:14.244
<i>- Point being, we were
fighting for the same work,</i>

30:14.246 --> 30:16.246
<i>and I would always hear,
"Oh, sorry.</i>

30:16.314 --> 30:17.981
<i>We've just booked Joss," or--</i>

30:18.049 --> 30:20.183
<i>- "We've just booked Jay,"
as the case may be.</i>

30:20.251 --> 30:21.985
I mean, it was
a little bit frustrating.

30:22.020 --> 30:23.821
We sensed that
we would do better as a duo.

30:23.855 --> 30:26.089
<i>- So we decided we'd try
working together,</i>

30:26.156 --> 30:28.291
<i>and we had a lot in common.</i>

30:28.359 --> 30:30.493
<i>- We'd perform together,
and then afterwards,</i>

30:30.561 --> 30:32.329
<i>we would just talk for hours.</i>

30:32.396 --> 30:33.864
<i>It was my dad
that pointed out to me,</i>

30:33.931 --> 30:36.633
<i>because he saw how happy Jay
and I were together.</i>

30:36.700 --> 30:38.468
London!

30:38.535 --> 30:41.805
And so he said,
"Are you two a couple?"

30:41.807 --> 30:45.275
<i>- We talked about it,
and then we realized,</i>

30:45.342 --> 30:47.644
"Yeah. I guess we are."

30:47.712 --> 30:52.282
<i>- So now, it's a partnership
onstage and in life,</i>

30:52.350 --> 30:54.517
and that's part
of what we're sharing here,

30:54.585 --> 30:55.819
on "Fool Us" tonight.

30:55.886 --> 30:57.287
<i>- The magic is, of course,
the main thing,</i>

30:57.355 --> 31:00.190
<i>so here comes Jay and Joss.</i>

31:01.158 --> 31:04.127
[cheers and applause]

31:04.962 --> 31:09.633
- Make way for the British
invasion of Jay and Joss!

31:09.635 --> 31:12.102
[cheers and applause]

31:12.169 --> 31:13.871
- Hey, guys.
We couldn't get to Vegas,

31:13.905 --> 31:16.439
so we thought we'd bring
a little bit of Vegas to us.

31:16.441 --> 31:21.378
- We're on vacation,
and we've pushed the boat out.

31:21.445 --> 31:22.812
- We can afford
to sit back and relax,

31:22.880 --> 31:24.814
as we done all the hard work
a few days ago

31:24.882 --> 31:26.516
when we recorded it
on Jay's phone

31:26.583 --> 31:28.118
while we were in the hot tub.

31:28.185 --> 31:29.619
- It's a hard life.

31:29.687 --> 31:31.655
- Penn, we think you've been
carrying the Penn and Teller

31:31.657 --> 31:34.524
show way too long,
and you deserve a break.

31:34.591 --> 31:37.827
- So we can't wait to see
the Alyson and Teller show

31:37.829 --> 31:39.562
when we get to Vegas.

31:39.630 --> 31:43.066
- What do you think?
- Good thinking.

31:43.133 --> 31:44.567
- Penn, don't worry.

31:44.635 --> 31:46.436
You've still got a crucial role
in this brand-new venture.

31:46.503 --> 31:48.605
You are gonna be playing
the wardrobe department

31:48.607 --> 31:51.741
for this new Vegas spectacular.
- Oh, boy.

31:51.809 --> 31:53.410
- Good.
- Penn?

31:53.477 --> 31:54.711
- Yeah.
- Teller? Alyson?

31:54.778 --> 31:56.680
Please join us onstage.

31:56.747 --> 31:58.548
Teller, please take
your jacket off.

32:00.217 --> 32:02.886
- And remember, guys,
we recorded this audio

32:02.954 --> 32:06.189
just over a week ago.
It's locked in the phone,

32:06.257 --> 32:08.625
and we're gonna just let you
guys get on with the work,

32:08.627 --> 32:11.194
while we get to work relaxing.

32:11.196 --> 32:13.563
We're gonna press play
on the audio.

32:13.565 --> 32:16.767
<i>Hey, Vegas. We're just
chilling in the hot tub</i>

32:16.834 --> 32:18.468
<i>and thought we'd record
this audio</i>

32:18.535 --> 32:20.170
<i>in advance, so that, on the day,</i>

32:20.237 --> 32:23.707
<i>we can concentrate
on topping up our tan.</i>

32:23.774 --> 32:25.809
<i>We've mailed over
some clothing and props,</i>

32:25.876 --> 32:27.277
<i>but as our designer, Penn,</i>

32:27.345 --> 32:29.679
<i>it's your job
to make some choices.</i>

32:29.747 --> 32:31.415
<i>- Penn, look at
the clothing rail now.</i>

32:33.451 --> 32:34.784
- Yep.

32:34.786 --> 32:37.420
<i>- Please reach forward
and grab one item.</i>

32:37.488 --> 32:41.491
<i>Hold it up with your left
or right hand.</i>

32:41.493 --> 32:42.926
- Pick a hand?
Okay. Right hand.

32:42.994 --> 32:44.861
<i>- Now, if you're holding
the item in your left hand,</i>

32:44.928 --> 32:46.463
<i>pass it to Teller to wear,</i>

32:46.530 --> 32:47.831
<i>and if it's in your right hand,</i>

32:47.898 --> 32:50.267
<i>then give it to Alyson to wear.</i>

32:50.334 --> 32:52.269
<i>Okay, Penn. Round two.</i>

32:52.336 --> 32:54.538
<i>Can you grab another item
from the rail,</i>

32:54.605 --> 32:57.274
<i>and hold it up in either
your left or right hand?</i>

32:59.777 --> 33:02.479
<i>This time, if you're holding
the item in your left hand,</i>

33:02.546 --> 33:03.947
<i>pass it to Alyson to wear.</i>

33:04.014 --> 33:05.181
<i>- And if it's in your
right hand,</i>

33:05.249 --> 33:07.317
<i>then Teller will wear it.</i>

33:07.384 --> 33:09.552
[audience exclaims]

33:09.554 --> 33:12.489
<i>- Okay. We're assuming
you've done that now.</i>

33:12.556 --> 33:14.224
- Yes.
<i>- Go on, Penn.</i>

33:14.291 --> 33:16.926
<i>Pick the third item.</i>

33:16.994 --> 33:19.596
<i>Just hold it in your left
or right hand.</i>

33:20.831 --> 33:22.165
<i>- We have faith.</i>

33:22.167 --> 33:25.435
<i>I'm sure you guys
are doing an amazing job.</i>

33:25.502 --> 33:27.504
[audience exclaims]
<i>- You know what to do.</i>

33:27.571 --> 33:30.173
<i>If the item's in your left
hand, pass it to Alyson.</i>

33:30.241 --> 33:32.308
<i>Right hand, give it to Teller.</i>

33:32.310 --> 33:33.710
<i>- The Penn and Teller costumes</i>

33:33.777 --> 33:36.179
<i>over the years,
haven't exactly been bold,</i>

33:36.247 --> 33:40.450
<i>so it's great to see Penn
letting loose.</i>

33:40.518 --> 33:44.687
<i>Penn, please pick up
another item from the rail.</i>

33:44.755 --> 33:47.424
<i>Now, it doesn't matter
which hand you hold it in,</i>

33:47.426 --> 33:49.526
<i>because we're going to decide.</i>

33:49.593 --> 33:53.397
<i>We think you should
give this to Teller.</i>

33:53.464 --> 33:56.733
- Yes.

33:56.735 --> 33:58.335
<i>- Three items left.</i>

33:58.402 --> 34:00.037
<i>Choose another one, Penn.</i>

34:02.873 --> 34:05.242
<i>- Penn, give this one
to Teller again.</i>

34:05.309 --> 34:06.743
- Oh, my gosh, Teller.

34:06.745 --> 34:09.479
<i>- Pick the penultimate item,
Penn.</i>

34:09.547 --> 34:11.247
<i>Hopefully you've got
this one by now.</i>

34:11.315 --> 34:12.749
- Yes I do.

34:12.751 --> 34:16.719
<i>- And this one will go
to Alyson this time.</i>

34:16.721 --> 34:18.822
<i>- Almost done.</i>
- Hey.

34:18.824 --> 34:20.190
<i>- Weird to think
that Alyson and Teller</i>

34:20.257 --> 34:22.158
<i>will be Vegas headliners
wearing crazy,</i>

34:22.226 --> 34:24.227
<i>childish outfits
made up of clothes</i>

34:24.295 --> 34:26.596
<i>you couldn't even give away
in a thrift store.</i>

34:26.663 --> 34:29.132
<i>- Finally, Penn,
pick up the last item,</i>

34:29.199 --> 34:30.867
<i>and give it to Alyson.</i>

34:31.969 --> 34:33.437
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

34:33.504 --> 34:35.371
<i>- Costume department,
you've done an amazing job.</i>

34:35.439 --> 34:37.440
<i>You can now leave the stage.</i>
- Thank you.

34:37.442 --> 34:41.377
<i>- Vegas stars,
Alyson and Teller!</i>

34:41.445 --> 34:43.180
[cheers and applause]

34:43.247 --> 34:44.347
- This looks brilliant.

34:44.414 --> 34:45.782
- You guys look amazing.

34:45.817 --> 34:47.984
- Penn, we think you've got
a new career ahead of you.

34:48.051 --> 34:49.319
- Thank you
- And while we've been sat here

34:49.353 --> 34:51.855
working on our tans,
sipping overpriced cocktails,

34:51.922 --> 34:53.190
for the last few minutes,

34:53.257 --> 34:54.757
we haven't even moved.

34:54.825 --> 34:57.461
- Now, Penn, remember you
dressed Alyson and Teller,

34:57.528 --> 35:00.563
and we have no idea which
clothes you would have picked.

35:00.631 --> 35:06.069
- But we already have
the merchandise...

35:06.136 --> 35:10.507
- For the brand new Alyson
and Teller show.

35:10.574 --> 35:14.544
[audience exclaims]
- All right. Whoo-hoo!

35:14.612 --> 35:18.014
[cheers and applause]

35:18.016 --> 35:19.783
- We've got a confession
to make.

35:21.952 --> 35:24.321
- We didn't get to go
very far on vacation.

35:29.960 --> 35:32.863
- But that doesn't stop us
from having fun.

35:33.764 --> 35:36.766
[upbeat music]

35:36.833 --> 35:43.807
♪ ♪

35:44.508 --> 35:50.013
- Jay and Joss!

35:50.080 --> 35:52.448
Hi, guys.

35:52.450 --> 35:53.917
Both: Hey.

35:53.984 --> 35:55.252
- I like my outfit.

35:55.319 --> 35:56.452
- Oh, you look amazing.

35:56.454 --> 35:57.754
- I've gotta say
you look incredible.

35:57.821 --> 35:59.789
- I definitely feel like
I'm ready to headline

35:59.857 --> 36:00.991
a Vegas show.

36:01.058 --> 36:02.825
So how did you two meet?

36:02.827 --> 36:06.796
- So I sold Lewis an illusion
six or seven years ago,

36:06.864 --> 36:09.533
and we met up again
at a magic convention.

36:09.600 --> 36:13.403
How romantic,
and we formed Jay and Joss.

36:13.405 --> 36:16.940
- Aw, so what was your
first performance together?

36:17.007 --> 36:20.043
- We actually put some of
the sort of information out

36:20.110 --> 36:21.544
before we had
the act ready to go.

36:21.546 --> 36:23.613
- We put the feelers out,
didn't we? Which was...

36:23.680 --> 36:24.681
- We--

36:24.748 --> 36:25.949
- The wrong way to do it,
because--

36:26.016 --> 36:27.016
- Well, we got booked and then
had to come up

36:27.018 --> 36:28.818
with some magic so.

36:28.886 --> 36:30.187
- To take that risk, you must

36:30.221 --> 36:32.388
have a lot of confidence
in each other.

36:32.456 --> 36:34.224
- 'Cause we know each other,
and live together,

36:34.291 --> 36:36.559
and work together,
and everything is together.

36:36.627 --> 36:38.495
We know each other inside-out,
so I think

36:38.562 --> 36:40.496
that definitely helps
when we're performing onstage.

36:40.498 --> 36:41.898
- All right, Jay and Joss.

36:41.900 --> 36:45.134
Let's see if you fooled
Penn and Teller.

36:45.202 --> 36:47.136
- Hey, Jay. Hey, Joss.
I've gotta tell you.

36:47.204 --> 36:50.106
You've solved
so many of our problems.

36:50.174 --> 36:53.843
For one, Teller finally,
finally looks like

36:53.911 --> 36:57.180
a real Vegas magician.
Perfectly done.

36:57.248 --> 36:58.982
And you've also solved
another problem,

36:59.049 --> 37:02.385
which is people complain
all the time

37:02.453 --> 37:06.889
that we--the three of us--wear
the same clothes every season,

37:06.957 --> 37:09.425
for the whole season.
You've now solved that.

37:09.493 --> 37:13.063
They can't say that anymore.
They can only say it about me,

37:13.130 --> 37:16.032
and I say that
with a certain amount of pride.

37:16.034 --> 37:19.569
We love double acts.
We love two-person acts.

37:19.636 --> 37:21.871
I know we got to be
a three-person act here,

37:21.938 --> 37:23.340
too, and so did you.

37:23.407 --> 37:27.410
You know what that's like,
to work with a group like that.

37:27.477 --> 37:30.246
We also loved your set with
the tree, and the branches,

37:30.248 --> 37:33.883
and all that going up was
really, really a funny routine.

37:33.885 --> 37:37.420
And I think Alyson--
Can we just keep that

37:37.487 --> 37:38.821
for the rest of the season?

37:38.823 --> 37:40.156
You look very, very good.

37:40.191 --> 37:44.160
Not as professional
Vegas magician as Teller does,

37:44.162 --> 37:46.262
but all the same,
very, very good.

37:46.264 --> 37:48.097
So you've solved
a lot of our problems.

37:48.165 --> 37:50.400
I think I put
a few things in there

37:50.467 --> 37:51.768
that should give you an idea
that we have

37:51.770 --> 37:53.903
a pretty good idea
how you did it,

37:53.905 --> 37:56.906
but we're very glad
you did do it.

37:56.973 --> 37:59.976
- Did they say enough to know
that you didn't fool them?

38:00.043 --> 38:02.812
- I think they got us.
- I think they got us.

38:02.879 --> 38:06.382
- All right. Well, thank you,
Jay and Joss!

38:06.450 --> 38:09.286
- Nicely done, Jay.
Nicely done, Joss.

38:11.888 --> 38:14.324
- We'll be right back with more
fabulous magic

38:14.391 --> 38:16.192
when "Fool Us" returns.

38:16.194 --> 38:18.594
[cheers and applause]

38:18.596 --> 38:20.630
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:23.734 --> 38:26.202
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:26.270 --> 38:28.571
[cheers and applause]

38:28.638 --> 38:31.107
- Welcome back. Penn and Teller
couldn't say goodbye

38:31.174 --> 38:33.509
without performing
a trick of their own,

38:33.577 --> 38:36.279
so take it away,
Penn and Teller!

38:36.346 --> 38:38.147
[cheers and applause]

38:38.215 --> 38:40.750
- We have a disagreement
with the New Testament.

38:40.818 --> 38:44.020
It says in there
it is easier for a camel

38:44.087 --> 38:46.155
to go through the eye
of a needle

38:46.223 --> 38:49.659
than for a rich man
to enter the kingdom of heaven.

38:49.726 --> 38:53.363
We do not agree,
and we can prove we are right.

38:53.430 --> 38:55.398
This is Kurt, and this is Zeke,

38:55.465 --> 38:57.834
and they are putting together
a cardboard box

38:57.836 --> 39:00.103
that will represent heaven.
Now, guys,

39:00.105 --> 39:03.306
make sure it is completely
impossible to get into.

39:03.308 --> 39:06.276
Cover every crack,
every cranny, every nook.

39:06.343 --> 39:09.278
Cover it all with tape
and with bubble wrap.

39:09.346 --> 39:12.549
